title.stringValue: Do you know how common asthma is in children?

response.stringValue: On average, 1 of every 12 school-aged children has asthma

That's roughly 6 million kids in America. Despite the fact that asthma is more common in women than in men, boys are more likely than girls to develop asthma. Whereas women who are 18 years or older are nearly twice as likely to have asthma than men
Also, a child is more likely to get asthma if other family members have it

response.stringValue: Exercise-induced asthma is actually called exercise-induced bronchoconstriction (EIB for short)

title.stringValue: It's an obstruction to the airway that happens because of exercise

response.stringValue: When you exercise, your body demands more oxygen, and you end up breathing faster and deeper than normal
During exercise, you typically breathe through your mouth (not your nose), causing the air reaching your lungs to be dryer and colder

title.stringValue: The cold and/or dry air is a key trigger for airway narrowing
